</number>
). Epandrium with anterodorsal and posterodorsal lobes of same height (
<figureCitation box="[1263,1344,983,1007]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Figs. 
<number box="[1328,1344,983,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="6.18">6</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1357,1387,983,1007]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1423,1446]" captionTargetBox="[272,1319,536,1402]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[267,1319,519,1402]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Macrostomus limbipennis (Bezzi), lectotype male. 12, left fore leg, posterior view; 13, left mid leg, anterior view; 14, left hind leg, anterior view; 15, right wing; 16 – 19, Peruvian male specimen; 16, wing; 17, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 18, terminalia, lateral view; 19, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 12 – 14 = 0.5 mm; 17 – 19 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281634/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">18</figureCitation>
, 
<number pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="30.37">
<figureCitation box="[1401,1431,983,1007]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1369,1392]" captionTargetBox="[262,1324,665,1345]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[260,1328,663,1345]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 31. Macrostomus nigriventris (Macquart), holotype. 26, right mid leg, posterior view; 27, left wing; 28, apex of medial lobe of cercus; 29, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 30 terminalia, lateral view, setae omitted; 31, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view, setae broken, insertion indicated. Scales: 26 = 0.5 mm; 28 – 31 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281636/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">30</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,183,1019,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">37</figureCitation>
</number>
). Hypandrium with variable setae, with apex narrow (
<figureCitation box="[781,860,1019,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Figs. 
<number box="[844,860,1020,1043]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="7.19">7</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[872,901,1019,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1423,1446]" captionTargetBox="[272,1319,536,1402]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[267,1319,519,1402]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Macrostomus limbipennis (Bezzi), lectotype male. 12, left fore leg, posterior view; 13, left mid leg, anterior view; 14, left hind leg, anterior view; 15, right wing; 16 – 19, Peruvian male specimen; 16, wing; 17, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 18, terminalia, lateral view; 19, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 12 – 14 = 0.5 mm; 17 – 19 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281634/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">19</figureCitation>
) or wide (
<figureCitation box="[1014,1107,1019,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1369,1392]" captionTargetBox="[262,1324,665,1345]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[260,1328,663,1345]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 31. Macrostomus nigriventris (Macquart), holotype. 26, right mid leg, posterior view; 27, left wing; 28, apex of medial lobe of cercus; 29, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 30 terminalia, lateral view, setae omitted; 31, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view, setae broken, insertion indicated. Scales: 26 = 0.5 mm; 28 – 31 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281636/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Figs. 
<number box="[1077,1107,1019,1043]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="31.38">31</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1118,1150,1019,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">38</figureCitation>
). Cercus divided into two lobes (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael" box="[272,563,1055,1079]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Rafael, J. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2004) The Neotropical genera Macrostomus Wiedemann and Porphyrochroa Melander (Diptera, Empididae, Empidinae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 21, 439 - 448." type="journal article" year="2004">
Rafael &amp; Cumming 
<number box="[505,563,1055,1079]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and an additional distinct median membranous lobe between them (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1421,1055,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Fig. 
<number box="[1405,1421,1055,1079]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); anterior cercus wide or narrow, connected anteriorly and medially by large flat cercal expansion; posterior cercus elongated. Phallus (
<figureCitation box="[371,449,1127,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Figs. 
<number box="[433,449,1128,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="7.19">7</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[461,491,1127,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1423,1446]" captionTargetBox="[272,1319,536,1402]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[267,1319,519,1402]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Macrostomus limbipennis (Bezzi), lectotype male. 12, left fore leg, posterior view; 13, left mid leg, anterior view; 14, left hind leg, anterior view; 15, right wing; 16 – 19, Peruvian male specimen; 16, wing; 17, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 18, terminalia, lateral view; 19, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 12 – 14 = 0.5 mm; 17 – 19 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281634/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">19</figureCitation>
, 
<number box="[502,573,1127,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="31.38">
<figureCitation box="[502,532,1127,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1369,1392]" captionTargetBox="[262,1324,665,1345]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[260,1328,663,1345]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 31. Macrostomus nigriventris (Macquart), holotype. 26, right mid leg, posterior view; 27, left wing; 28, apex of medial lobe of cercus; 29, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 30 terminalia, lateral view, setae omitted; 31, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view, setae broken, insertion indicated. Scales: 26 = 0.5 mm; 28 – 31 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281636/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">31</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[544,573,1127,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">38</figureCitation>
</number>
) as long as hypandrium, with apical portion of endophallus slightly projected beyond sheath (
<figureCitation box="[327,411,1163,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Fig. 
<number box="[380,411,1163,1187]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="38.0">38</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme tetralamelar (
<figureCitation box="[824,892,1163,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Fig. 
<number box="[876,892,1163,1187]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,581,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1199,1223]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Female</emphasis>
. Head dichoptic; frons wider than anterior ocellus width; face narrower than frons, approximately half of anterior ocellus width. Legs with no pinnate scales; hind tarsomere 
<number box="[940,954,1235,1259]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
with one dorsal setae. Wing slightly wider than in male, usually more infuscated at costal and distal margin. Terminalia less shining and more gray pruinose than preabdomen. Tergite 
<number box="[444,458,1307,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="8.0">8</number>
elongate. Sternite 
<number box="[667,681,1307,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="8.0">8</number>
usually with median large sinus, laterally with ventral constriction. Genital fork with short to indistinct lateral arms. Spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[859,940,1343,1367]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 25" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1184,1207]" captionTargetBox="[274,1332,485,1142]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[252,1334,483,1160]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 25. Macrostomus limbipennis (Bezzi), 20 – 25, Peruvian female specimen; 20, wing; 21, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 22, idem, lateral view; 23, idem, except cercus, ventral view; 24, genital fork and genital chamber; 25, oviduct and spermathecae. Scales: 21 – 23 = 0.2 mm; 24 – 25 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281635/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Fig. 
<number box="[911,940,1343,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) with long duct and rounded receptacle.
</paragraph>
